44:24.667 --> 44:26.749
One of us will use physical
violence against one of the others

44:26.750 --> 44:28.541
- before the week's out.
- OK.

44:28.542 --> 44:30.249
This holiday is going
to be a disaster.

44:30.250 --> 44:31.457
Oh, I hope so.

44:31.458 --> 44:33.374
So, who's looking
after Matty, Maureen?

44:33.375 --> 44:35.499
No one. She's just left
some food in the fridge

44:35.500 --> 44:37.901
and some wet wipes by the bed.

44:38.125 --> 44:40.082
I'm sure the break will do
you both the world of good.

44:40.083 --> 44:41.666
- Yeah, that's what Dr Stephens said.
- Yeah. Yeah.

44:41.667 --> 44:43.166
- He's taken him for a week's observation.
- Yeah, yeah.

44:43.167 --> 44:45.332
- Your boarding pass, Madam.
- Yeah, go ahead.

44:45.333 --> 44:47.749
Your boarding pass, with
your flight details on it.

44:47.750 --> 44:49.855
You were handed it at check-in.

44:50.375 --> 44:51.916
This?

44:51.917 --> 44:53.999
And your passport.

44:54.000 --> 44:55.557
OK.

45:03.417 --> 45:05.143
There you go.

45:11.625 --> 45:13.124
Thank you very much.

45:13.125 --> 45:14.832
Maureen? Maureen!

45:14.833 --> 45:16.541
- Uh, no, sorry. You can't go backwards.
- Maureen, stop.

45:16.542 --> 45:17.999
Please stop, Maureen.
Please, please stop.

45:18.000 --> 45:19.749
It's just a trip, that's all.

45:19.750 --> 45:22.624
Just a trip, till all this
press nonsense blows over.

45:22.625 --> 45:25.791
- It's for the best.
- This is all... It's just all too much.

45:25.792 --> 45:27.416
I mean, I don't know you.

45:27.417 --> 45:29.853
And I don't travel
well. And I've...

45:30.625 --> 45:32.249
I've never been on a 'plane before.

45:32.250 --> 45:35.350
- You've never been on a 'plane before?
- Shut up, Jess.

45:35.667 --> 45:38.374
Maureen, if you're afraid of
flying, I've got these tablets.

45:38.375 --> 45:41.653
I'm not afraid of
flying. It's just, I'm...

45:41.750 --> 45:44.666
I didn't want to be in the papers
and I didn't want to be on TV,

45:44.667 --> 45:47.374
and I don't want to
be here now. I just...

45:47.375 --> 45:50.475
I just want to go back
to my old life, OK?

45:50.875 --> 45:54.070
But your old life wasn't
very good, Maureen.

45:54.833 --> 45:56.666
Look, we made a pact.

45:56.667 --> 46:02.041
This is the final call for
Flight CA432 to Tenerife.

46:02.042 --> 46:05.332
Will all remaining passengers
please make their way to Gate C38

46:05.333 --> 46:07.604
- immediately.
- It's gonna be fine.

46:09.375 --> 46:11.065
Come on.

46:42.292 --> 46:45.666
- To a really good holiday.
- To life.

46:45.667 --> 46:46.999
Good afternoon.

46:47.000 --> 46:49.916
My name is Angelo and
I will be your waiter.

46:49.917 --> 46:53.432
Well, sometimes I will.
Other times I will be theirs.

46:54.792 --> 46:57.124
It's just a joke. Real, but a joke.

46:57.125 --> 46:58.874
Hello, Angelo.

46:58.875 --> 47:00.707
So, you're from England? How nice.

47:00.708 --> 47:02.999
Yeah, you knew that, Angelo.
You just talked English to us.

47:03.000 --> 47:05.436
I did, I did.

47:05.667 --> 47:07.291
Is he always this
clever, your husband?

47:07.292 --> 47:09.166
He is not her husband.

47:09.167 --> 47:10.791
Let me guess.

47:10.792 --> 47:12.457
- You're all lovers, right?
- What? No.

47:12.458 --> 47:14.416
- Yes, yes.
- Yeah, yeah.

47:14.417 --> 47:15.707
Yeah, we are, right here.

47:15.708 --> 47:18.856
I bring Vaseline and Maureen
always brings a dildo.

47:19.375 --> 47:22.166
You know, someone told me
a joke about Vaseline once.

47:22.167 --> 47:24.457
But I can't entirely remember it.

47:24.458 --> 47:26.791
Well, Maureen, you must keep
drinking till you remember.

47:26.792 --> 47:28.457
Yeah.

47:28.458 --> 47:30.893
- We're happy. Good.
- Me, too.

47:46.500 --> 47:49.832
Oh, the sun is so fierce.

47:49.833 --> 47:52.749
And the sea's so sparkly and blue.

47:52.750 --> 47:55.707
Oh, Maureen, tell me that
you've seen the sea before.

47:55.708 --> 47:57.791
Yes, I've seen the sea before.

47:57.792 --> 47:59.124
Are we going in?

47:59.125 --> 48:00.749
- No.
- Of course we are.

48:00.750 --> 48:03.601
- We're not in our swimming costumes.
- Oh, underwear will be fine.

48:04.958 --> 48:06.582
- You don't see... No, no!
- Come on.

48:06.583 --> 48:08.249
No!

48:08.250 --> 48:10.983
Come on, grab her!
Come on, grab her!

48:45.250 --> 48:47.568
- Hi.
- Hey.

48:47.583 --> 48:49.605
- Hi.
- Hey.

48:53.833 --> 48:56.291
Maureen just called me
up on the hotel 'phone.

48:56.292 --> 48:59.356
Surprised to have her own bathroom.

48:59.542 --> 49:04.147
- She thinks this place is the height of luxury.
- Yeah, it is kind of cool, huh?

49:05.042 --> 49:07.893
Cheapest place I've
stayed in for 20 years.

49:08.375 --> 49:09.916
Yeah?

49:09.917 --> 49:12.401
It doesn't feel strange, does it?

49:12.750 --> 49:14.291
Us...

49:14.292 --> 49:16.749
- Being away together?
- No.

49:16.750 --> 49:18.332
No, it feels good.

49:18.333 --> 49:21.791
I thought I knew what I was
doing with the press and then...

49:21.792 --> 49:23.207
And then what?

49:23.208 --> 49:25.166
- The Jess meltdown and...
- No, no, no.

49:25.167 --> 49:29.061
Then I realised I'd got it all
wrong. I thought people would like it.

49:29.333 --> 49:31.916
I thought we'd make money and
people would find it eccentric

49:31.917 --> 49:34.166
- and heart-warming.
- Heart-warming?

49:34.167 --> 49:39.749
Four people survive suicide,
find hope, blah, blah, you know.

49:39.750 --> 49:43.312
I mean, it's the kind of
good-news story the press love.

49:46.500 --> 49:48.143
However,

49:49.667 --> 49:52.482
I underestimated how
much they hate me.

49:52.750 --> 49:55.649
It's not just about you, Martin.

49:56.208 --> 49:58.230
You know,

49:59.083 --> 50:01.022
I envy you.

50:01.375 --> 50:05.103
You, your cancer. I
mean, it's so cut and dry.

50:05.417 --> 50:09.666
No, really. Really, JJ, I
am so impressed with you.

50:09.667 --> 50:12.400
I mean, you hardly
let it phase you.

50:12.583 --> 50:14.832
And that is something to drink to.

50:14.833 --> 50:16.985
Here you go.

50:17.583 --> 50:19.522
Put hairs on your chest.

50:23.417 --> 50:25.320
Your health.

50:29.917 --> 50:33.148
Do you know what I feel when
I wake up in the mornings?

50:35.375 --> 50:37.314
Humiliated.

50:39.083 --> 50:41.520
Do you know what I
feel at lunchtime?

50:42.000 --> 50:43.643
Humiliated.

50:44.167 --> 50:48.499
My life is a constant
stream of humiliation.

50:48.500 --> 50:51.778
I don't feel sad. I don't
feel angry. I just feel...

50:52.667 --> 50:54.523
Humiliated.

50:56.583 --> 50:58.226
Yeah.

50:58.958 --> 51:01.229
To humiliation.

51:05.375 --> 51:09.416
OK, God gives you three wishes.

51:09.417 --> 51:12.541
Oh, God's not a
tombola machine, Martin.

51:12.542 --> 51:15.124
He doesn't just give wishes.

51:15.125 --> 51:16.916
Three wishes. Anything you want.

51:16.917 --> 51:18.957
That's easy. OK, billions of pounds

51:18.958 --> 51:22.749
- and my own personal hitman...
- OK.

51:22.750 --> 51:25.916
and a court waiver

51:25.917 --> 51:28.401
over anything that I want to do.

51:29.000 --> 51:31.520
- Really? Um...
- Mmm-hmm.

51:31.750 --> 51:36.225
Well, I'd... I'd
want a bit more help.

51:36.667 --> 51:39.103
A bit more of a life.

51:39.375 --> 51:41.374
What's a bit more of a life?

51:41.375 --> 51:43.895
Just what other people have.

51:44.083 --> 51:47.397
What do other people have?

51:47.542 --> 51:49.582
And I'd wish my son all better.

51:49.583 --> 51:51.735
That's why I don't do wishes.

51:53.750 --> 51:57.541
I'd want to be famous again,
the right kind of famous.

51:57.542 --> 51:59.457
I mean, being famous is great.

51:59.458 --> 52:01.707
Everyone think it's
difficult, but it's not.

52:01.708 --> 52:04.457
I mean, you get to have the
best seats in restaurants.

52:04.458 --> 52:08.041
People smile at you
on 'planes. It's great.

52:08.042 --> 52:12.332
And whatever you do, you feel
vindicated by your own fame.

52:12.333 --> 52:16.061
And you never ever feel humiliated.

52:17.000 --> 52:20.457
Well, it's certainly better
than real life, anyway.

52:20.458 --> 52:22.249
Wow!

52:22.250 --> 52:24.355
You're so deep.

52:24.500 --> 52:26.624
No, I'm just honest.

52:26.625 --> 52:28.999
- Martin! It's...
- What?

52:29.000 --> 52:30.707
You're nothing if
you're not noticed.

52:30.708 --> 52:33.109
OK, fame or your kids?

52:34.500 --> 52:36.541
- Mmm...
- Martin, you don't mean that.

52:36.542 --> 52:38.249
Don't I?

52:38.250 --> 52:42.109
All right, this is a bad game.

52:47.292 --> 52:49.100
OK.

52:49.375 --> 52:53.400
I wonder what JJ would
choose as his three wishes.

52:54.167 --> 52:56.082
'Cos, obviously, you'd...

52:56.083 --> 52:59.397
