58:07.667 --> 58:09.374
That is intense.

58:09.375 --> 58:12.749
- What... What was the... real reason?
- I...

58:12.750 --> 58:14.938
You know what? I don't know.

58:14.958 --> 58:18.355
I do know that I am
now part of a pact

58:18.458 --> 58:22.318
- that I had to lie to become a...
- What pact?

58:23.833 --> 58:25.559
Just a...

58:26.208 --> 58:29.749
Just a bunch of desperate
people being desperate together

58:29.750 --> 58:33.194
as a way of feeling a
little less desperate.

58:35.333 --> 58:38.149
OK, you win the psycho game.

58:38.958 --> 58:43.184
Good. Good. I always
wanted to win that game.

59:00.167 --> 59:02.916
I haven't done this
for a while, so...

59:02.917 --> 59:04.643
Mmm.

59:46.458 --> 59:48.999
- OK, now I'm going to say something.
- Oh, fuck!

59:49.000 --> 59:51.082
Because if I wait and say
nothing and then you spot me

59:51.083 --> 59:53.707
after you've pissed, I think
that would probably be worse.

59:53.708 --> 59:55.957
Wait, how did...
How did you even...

59:55.958 --> 59:57.832
Just took a credit card
and a bit of spit, you know.

59:57.833 --> 01:00:00.851
Hotel security is
not what it should be.

01:00:01.458 --> 01:00:03.776
How long have you been there?

01:00:06.958 --> 01:00:12.582
I just really wanted to
apologise for earlier.

01:00:12.583 --> 01:00:13.874
Because I don't know...

01:00:13.875 --> 01:00:15.897
I don't know why I said that.

01:00:16.625 --> 01:00:19.394
And then I was probably
gonna try and shag you.

01:00:21.375 --> 01:00:23.499
She's really pretty, though,

01:00:23.500 --> 01:00:24.666
So, well done.

01:00:24.667 --> 01:00:25.832
- Hey...
- You don't have to say anything.

01:00:25.833 --> 01:00:29.645
You can take that one
as a compliment.

01:00:29.667 --> 01:00:33.110
Then, I'll just leave quietly.

01:00:34.375 --> 01:00:35.541
Hey, uh, Jess...

01:00:35.542 --> 01:00:39.685
You know, I really would prefer
it if you didn't say anything.

01:00:41.833 --> 01:00:44.649
You do know she's a
journalist though, right?

01:00:45.542 --> 01:00:47.528
- What?
- Look in her bag.

01:00:47.750 --> 01:00:51.360
'Cos I saw her check
her recorder in the bar.

01:00:52.542 --> 01:00:56.934
- Oh, my God!
- Still, she fucked you, though, right?

01:00:57.958 --> 01:01:00.608
So, at least she's thorough.

01:01:02.333 --> 01:01:03.941
Hey, hey.

01:01:12.958 --> 01:01:14.332
"What pact?"

01:01:14.333 --> 01:01:17.999
"Just... just a bunch
of desperate people

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:20.124
"being desperate together

01:01:20.125 --> 01:01:22.724
"as a way of feeling a
little less desperate."

01:03:12.417 --> 01:03:14.439
I think it's sweet.

01:03:14.792 --> 01:03:16.666
I think it's unsanitary.

01:03:16.667 --> 01:03:20.041
No, only part of you thinks that.
The other part thinks it's sweet.

01:03:20.042 --> 01:03:22.749
Oh... Hmm.

01:03:22.750 --> 01:03:24.916
- Why are you waiting here?
- I'm waiting for them to finish

01:03:24.917 --> 01:03:27.666
this tray of scrambled egg
and bring in a new tray.

01:03:27.667 --> 01:03:30.666
But the scrambled egg's
never fresh, Martin.

01:03:30.667 --> 01:03:32.541
I mean, I might not have
been on a lot of holidays,

01:03:32.542 --> 01:03:36.436
but I've been in a lot of hospitals
and I understand institutional catering.

01:03:37.458 --> 01:03:41.021
Who are all these people
and why do they eat so much?

01:03:41.375 --> 01:03:43.977
They're having a
good time, that's all.

01:03:47.250 --> 01:03:49.355
- Martin.
- Hmm?

01:03:49.625 --> 01:03:52.275
Thank you for
arranging this holiday.

01:03:52.292 --> 01:03:53.749
I think it's been good for me.

01:03:53.750 --> 01:03:58.106
You really don't understand what
a disaster we all are, do you?

01:03:58.542 --> 01:04:03.624
- Come on, let's get you some breakfast.
- Yeah, good idea, good idea.

01:04:03.625 --> 01:04:07.318
- The prunes are very good.
- Don't like prunes.

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:30.733
- Hi.
- Oh, morning, JJ.

01:04:31.083 --> 01:04:33.476
I may have said some
stupid things last night.

01:04:33.500 --> 01:04:34.916
Drink has never been my friend.

01:04:34.917 --> 01:04:38.499
- Sorry about that.
- So, I got a few things to say.

01:04:38.500 --> 01:04:41.832
I don't think you're
gonna like any of them.

01:04:41.833 --> 01:04:43.082
Are you going back to America?

01:04:43.083 --> 01:04:46.646
Yeah, I'm gonna start with
the... the biggest... Um...

01:04:46.792 --> 01:04:51.291
I don't have cancer of the... the brain.

01:04:51.292 --> 01:04:53.957
- I don't have CCR.
- Oh, they've cured you!

01:04:53.958 --> 01:04:58.332
No, Maureen, I,
uh... I never had it.

01:04:58.333 --> 01:05:00.832
- I... I made it all up.
- Oh.

01:05:00.833 --> 01:05:04.291
There's actually no
such thing as... as CCR.

01:05:04.292 --> 01:05:06.499
It's just Creedence
Clearwater Revival are

01:05:06.500 --> 01:05:07.999
one of my favourite bands, but...

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:10.582
Oh. I wasn't gonna say anything.

01:05:10.583 --> 01:05:11.749
Did you know about this?

01:05:11.750 --> 01:05:13.457
You know, I thought there
was something strange.

01:05:13.458 --> 01:05:15.582
So, why, hmm?

01:05:15.583 --> 01:05:17.166
Why, JJ, were you up there?

01:05:17.167 --> 01:05:18.832
He can't answer
that. That's personal.

01:05:18.833 --> 01:05:22.499
- I'm sure he had good reasons.
- Oh, did he? JJ, did you?

01:05:22.500 --> 01:05:24.403
Yeah, um...

01:05:25.667 --> 01:05:29.957
Guys, actually, I'm gonna need
to postpone this conversation...

01:05:29.958 --> 01:05:32.166
We... We had a pact.

01:05:32.167 --> 01:05:35.082
I... I trusted you. I liked you!

01:05:35.083 --> 01:05:37.582
Hey, Martin, please, just sit down.
We'll talk about this another time.

01:05:37.583 --> 01:05:40.980
- Another time? What time would you...
- Hey, where were you?

01:05:41.292 --> 01:05:44.249
Oh, right, great. We all stop
for your girlfriend, do we?

01:05:44.250 --> 01:05:47.666
She's not my girlfriend,
OK? She's...

01:05:47.667 --> 01:05:51.124
- She's a journalist.
- What?

01:05:51.125 --> 01:05:52.624
- Look, I didn't know.
- Shit.

01:05:52.625 --> 01:05:54.207
You don't know much, do you?

01:05:54.208 --> 01:05:56.582
If he didn't know, he didn't know.

01:05:56.583 --> 01:05:58.874
I mean, we've had bad things
written about us before.

01:05:58.875 --> 01:06:03.041
Look, I understand that you
are angry, but, please, Martin,

01:06:03.042 --> 01:06:05.832
- I'm feeling pretty humiliated...
- Oh, you don't understand anything!

01:06:05.833 --> 01:06:07.832
You certainly don't
understand humiliation!

01:06:07.833 --> 01:06:10.666
- Martin, you're being dramatic.
- You're a leech! You're a fake!

01:06:10.667 --> 01:06:13.457
- You're a fraud! You're a joke, JJ.
- Martin, stop this.

01:06:13.458 --> 01:06:15.791
- John...
- Who the fuck is John?

01:06:15.792 --> 01:06:18.082
I'm... Look, I'm John.

01:06:18.083 --> 01:06:19.582
And you know what?

01:06:19.583 --> 01:06:22.291
- I'm not a fraud.
- Stop it. Remember the pact.

01:06:22.292 --> 01:06:24.563
Fuck the pact!

01:06:25.250 --> 01:06:26.891
I'm not a fraud!

01:06:32.292 --> 01:06:35.060
Don't you ever touch me again!

01:07:34.625 --> 01:07:37.061
Good morning, sunshine.

01:07:37.542 --> 01:07:39.528
Hello, sweetheart.

01:07:40.750 --> 01:07:43.541
Hello, sleepy head.

01:07:43.542 --> 01:07:46.791
How are you? Good morning.

01:07:46.792 --> 01:07:48.541
All right, here we go.

01:07:48.542 --> 01:07:50.707
"Not having Matty with
me on the holiday,

01:07:50.708 --> 01:07:53.559
"it... it felt like
I was missing a leg.

01:07:54.083 --> 01:07:55.892
"Strange.

01:07:56.500 --> 01:07:58.226
"Light.

01:07:58.500 --> 01:08:01.434
"That's probably not
like missing a leg at all.

01:08:01.625 --> 01:08:04.374
"I don't imagine most
people's first impressions

01:08:04.375 --> 01:08:06.563
"of leg loss is weightlessness."

01:08:13.292 --> 01:08:15.195
How's that?

01:08:15.542 --> 01:08:17.184
There we are.

01:08:20.917 --> 01:08:24.041
"I missed him most when
the 'plane was landing.

01:08:24.042 --> 01:08:26.147
"We shook a little on descent.

01:08:26.707 --> 01:08:28.777
"I thought I was going to die.

01:08:29.417 --> 01:08:31.818
"And I hadn't said goodbye.

01:08:50.957 --> 01:08:56.060
"JJ's girlfriend's piece meant
the story, our story, didn't die.

01:08:56.417 --> 01:08:58.499
"But Martin said to
concentrate on being boring

01:08:58.500 --> 01:09:00.901
"and they'd eventually
leave us alone.

01:09:01.250 --> 01:09:04.647
"So, that's what I
did. Not difficult.

01:09:04.957 --> 01:09:07.207
"And, as for the others,

01:09:07.207 --> 01:09:11.916
"as soon as we landed, we scattered
in different directions like we were

01:09:11.917 --> 01:09:14.152
"allergic to each other.

01:09:14.500 --> 01:09:16.666
"The pact was broken beyond repair,

01:09:16.667 --> 01:09:20.644
"and without the pact, our
friendship was broken, too.

01:09:23.082 --> 01:09:26.729
"I still saw them, actually,
every now and again.

01:09:28.542 --> 01:09:32.685
"I saw Jess in places
she shouldn't be.

01:09:33.667 --> 01:09:37.277
"And I did make a
little effort to find JJ,

01:09:38.332 --> 01:09:39.916
"just to check he was OK."

01:09:39.917 --> 01:09:45.269
JJ, I can't believe...
One last time, slower!

01:09:49.332 --> 01:09:51.687
"I never saw Martin.

01:09:55.083 --> 01:09:58.397
"No, mostly, I...
I got on with my life

01:09:59.042 --> 01:10:01.857
"and hoped they
got on with theirs."

01:10:16.333 --> 01:10:18.734
Matty did really well.

01:10:18.958 --> 01:10:21.727
We did some
interesting reflex work.

01:10:22.417 --> 01:10:26.249
Nice to have him properly
looked after for once.

01:10:26.250 --> 01:10:28.124
He reacted well to company.

01:10:28.125 --> 01:10:30.624
I'm sure he loved a change
from my blathering.

01:10:30.625 --> 01:10:33.275
We couldn't get him
out of this pool.

01:10:33.375 --> 01:10:35.124
Well, he's always loved water.

01:10:35.125 --> 01:10:36.916
You know, er, there might be a

01:10:36.917 --> 01:10:41.143
slot for him to come to one of my
weekly sessions, if you'd like it.

01:10:41.708 --> 01:10:44.310
Oh, I'm sure he'd love it.

01:10:44.542 --> 01:10:46.610
I'll add him to the list.

01:10:46.750 --> 01:10:50.894
You know, you look like
you've caught a bit of colour.

01:10:51.417 --> 01:10:53.439
Do I?

01:10:55.500 --> 01:10:58.582
You know, from the
pictures in the papers,

01:10:58.583 --> 01:11:03.153
it looked like you
picked a very nice spot.

01:11:04.875 --> 01:11:06.482
Yes.

01:11:06.792 --> 01:11:08.600
Well...

01:11:45.292 --> 01:11:51.734
♪ Inchworm
measuring the marigolds

01:11:52.250 --> 01:11:56.416
♪ You and your arithmetic

01:11:56.417 --> 01:12:00.726
♪ You'll probably go far

01:12:01.292 --> 01:12:05.684
♪ Two and two are four

01:12:06.208 --> 01:12:10.731
♪ Four and four are eight

