♪ Eight and eight are 16

01:12:15.250 --> 01:12:20.271
♪ 16 and 16 are 32 ♪

01:12:46.167 --> 01:12:47.940
Matty?

01:12:48.250 --> 01:12:50.236
Matty.

01:12:50.792 --> 01:12:52.695
Matty.

01:12:54.583 --> 01:12:57.778
No. No.

01:13:04.458 --> 01:13:06.148
Matty?

01:13:08.375 --> 01:13:10.397
Oh, Matty!

01:13:23.167 --> 01:13:26.267
We'll let you know as soon
as there's any information.

01:14:03.500 --> 01:14:07.359
- Hey, Maureen.
- Oh!

01:14:10.875 --> 01:14:13.146
Ah...

01:14:22.042 --> 01:14:25.416
Oh, you came, too!

01:14:25.417 --> 01:14:28.232
Yeah. Nothing on TV.

01:14:28.667 --> 01:14:32.608
Uh, this is my dad. He drove me.

01:14:32.625 --> 01:14:34.291
He'll probably say
something very moving.

01:14:34.292 --> 01:14:36.541
I'm sorry to hear
about your son, Maureen.

01:14:36.542 --> 01:14:40.401
It's not one of his
best attempts, is it?

01:14:41.083 --> 01:14:44.166
I'm really... I'm really
grateful you're all...

01:14:44.167 --> 01:14:46.624
You're all here.

01:14:46.625 --> 01:14:48.481
Of course we're here.

01:14:54.083 --> 01:14:55.749
This isn't tea.

01:14:55.750 --> 01:14:56.957
No, I know. It's hot chocolate.

01:14:56.958 --> 01:14:58.624
- But I asked for tea.
- Well, I was buying

01:14:58.625 --> 01:15:00.624
and I don't like the smell of tea.

01:15:00.625 --> 01:15:03.524
- So, when you buy rounds in pubs...
- Pink gins.

01:15:03.917 --> 01:15:05.707
Then you never have to
buy a round ever again.

01:15:05.708 --> 01:15:07.499
It's clever, right, hmm?

01:15:07.500 --> 01:15:09.356
Is JJ still not here, then?

01:15:09.750 --> 01:15:11.916
I... I couldn't get through to him.

01:15:11.917 --> 01:15:13.874
He's probably not
picked up his messages.

01:15:13.875 --> 01:15:16.499
Yeah, it's either that or he doesn't
really care. It's one or the other.

01:15:16.500 --> 01:15:19.332
I genuinely don't know
how you've survived her.

01:15:19.333 --> 01:15:21.041
- Ear plugs.
- I am going to make you

01:15:21.042 --> 01:15:22.374
go and sit in the car in a minute.

01:15:22.375 --> 01:15:24.791
Ear plugs and pink gin.

01:15:24.792 --> 01:15:27.477
He wasn't the reason
I was up there.

01:15:27.625 --> 01:15:29.232
Matty.

01:15:30.167 --> 01:15:31.856
He wasn't.

01:15:33.208 --> 01:15:34.768
No?

01:15:35.417 --> 01:15:38.778
There were lots of reasons
I was up on that roof.

01:15:39.917 --> 01:15:42.851
You once asked me why, Jess.

01:15:43.750 --> 01:15:47.727
And... I said... I
said I felt helpless.

01:15:53.250 --> 01:15:58.271
But the truth is, I'd not... I'd not
done a list for living and a list for...

01:15:59.875 --> 01:16:04.019
It... It was a
feeling. Not a thought.

01:16:06.917 --> 01:16:09.188
But not one of those reasons

01:16:11.333 --> 01:16:14.067
was that I didn't love my son.

01:16:14.125 --> 01:16:16.349
Not one of them, not one.

01:16:22.917 --> 01:16:25.271
Maureen, we know that.

01:16:32.583 --> 01:16:37.249
Oh, God! Oh, no, no, no, no, no...

01:16:37.250 --> 01:16:38.541
- No, no, no.
- Don't tell me...

01:16:38.542 --> 01:16:40.666
He's fine. Maureen. Maureen...

01:16:40.667 --> 01:16:42.570
He's fine.

01:16:43.250 --> 01:16:45.166
- What?
- We're gonna keep monitoring him.

01:16:45.167 --> 01:16:47.235
But he's no longer critical.

01:16:47.458 --> 01:16:50.416
- He'll be fine.
- He'll be fine?

01:16:50.417 --> 01:16:53.057
- Yeah, he'll be fine.
- OK.

01:16:54.542 --> 01:16:56.707
Now, the tubes look
worse than they are.

01:16:56.708 --> 01:16:59.832
We'll remove some tonight and the
rest, hopefully, will be out tomorrow.

01:16:59.833 --> 01:17:03.541
Oh! I should have seen it coming.

01:17:03.542 --> 01:17:05.999
If he'd had... If he'd
had proper care then...

01:17:06.000 --> 01:17:10.060
Maureen... you saved him.

01:17:10.500 --> 01:17:13.316
It was a myocardial infarction.

01:17:14.958 --> 01:17:17.499
He... He had a heart
attack of sorts.

01:17:17.500 --> 01:17:19.901
His symptoms were almost invisible.

01:17:20.792 --> 01:17:25.397
I didn't notice it. I was
monitoring it and I didn't...

01:17:26.667 --> 01:17:28.819
But you caught it.

01:17:29.375 --> 01:17:31.610
You saved his life.

01:17:36.458 --> 01:17:38.813
Matty's a very lucky
boy to have you.

01:17:41.042 --> 01:17:43.277
I only had one thought.

01:17:44.417 --> 01:17:46.190
When he...

01:17:48.542 --> 01:17:51.855
If he dies, I die.

01:17:53.542 --> 01:17:55.729
Well, he lived.

01:17:59.625 --> 01:18:05.309
And maybe he feels the same way
about you as you do about him.

01:18:06.583 --> 01:18:08.901
Have you ever considered that?

01:18:19.542 --> 01:18:21.832
- It's Valentine's Day.
- Mmm-hmm.

01:18:21.833 --> 01:18:22.999
- Martin.
- Yeah?

01:18:23.000 --> 01:18:24.957
- Today is Valentine's Day.
- Good.

01:18:24.958 --> 01:18:26.166
- Martin.
- Yeah.

01:18:26.167 --> 01:18:29.541
Breakfast TV's completely messed
up your brain, hasn't it? Come on.

01:18:29.542 --> 01:18:32.999
- Oh, JJ! The pact!
- Get Maureen. I'm gonna find JJ now.

01:18:33.000 --> 01:18:35.235
Yeah. Oh, shit.

01:18:57.458 --> 01:19:00.582
Have you... Have you seen JJ?

01:19:00.583 --> 01:19:02.624
JJ is gone.

01:19:02.625 --> 01:19:04.374
- Gone?
- Yeah, he's a prick.

01:19:04.375 --> 01:19:07.902
He left over a week ago.
He didn't even serve notice.

01:19:08.125 --> 01:19:14.235
That prick you're talking about, Paolo,
happens to be my daughter's friend.

01:19:14.917 --> 01:19:17.069
And you'd do well to remember that.

01:19:24.375 --> 01:19:26.807
You are called Paolo, aren't you?

01:19:29.542 --> 01:19:32.903
It's just that it says
Paolo's Place outside and you

01:19:33.375 --> 01:19:37.519
certainly sound Italian.
You look Italian and...

01:19:39.583 --> 01:19:42.518
- Love your tats.
- Come on, Dad.

01:19:50.583 --> 01:19:53.707
- Hello?
- Oh, er... yes. Hi, hi, hello.

01:19:53.708 --> 01:19:56.275
- What?
- I'm looking for JJ.

01:19:56.708 --> 01:19:59.559
- Who?
- John Julius.

01:20:20.083 --> 01:20:21.691
Oh, JJ.

01:21:36.292 --> 01:21:38.479
I hoped you wouldn't be up here.

01:21:40.792 --> 01:21:44.791
You know, three people have killed
themselves from this building

01:21:44.792 --> 01:21:47.063
between New Year's and today?

01:21:48.375 --> 01:21:53.478
Sue Chalmott, housewife
and manic depressive.

01:21:53.750 --> 01:21:58.749
Um, David Frommet, banker
who lost everything.

01:21:58.750 --> 01:22:03.916
And, er, Ben Peterson.
He was only 15.

01:22:03.917 --> 01:22:07.749
So, you're going to join them?

01:22:07.750 --> 01:22:10.249
I kept to the pact, Martin, OK?

01:22:10.250 --> 01:22:14.192
This, me, it's none
of your business now.

01:22:14.333 --> 01:22:19.354
True. Why, though, JJ?
Why are you up here?

01:22:19.958 --> 01:22:25.394
That's the thing, Martin.
I... I didn't lie to you.

01:22:25.708 --> 01:22:29.749
- I don't know.
- You... don't know?

01:22:29.750 --> 01:22:33.124
And that makes my reason
better than any of yours.

01:22:33.125 --> 01:22:36.190
I wasn't aware that
this was a competition.

01:22:37.250 --> 01:22:42.152
You see, all Jess needs
is to feel important.

01:22:43.042 --> 01:22:47.944
Maureen, she needs to feel loved.

01:22:49.000 --> 01:22:53.570
And you, you just... You
just need to grow a brain.

01:22:54.750 --> 01:22:56.440
Fair enough.

01:22:56.958 --> 01:23:01.896
See, you can solve your
problems, but me, I can't.

01:23:02.208 --> 01:23:03.749
Just, Martin... Martin, stop.

01:23:03.750 --> 01:23:08.439
Martin, just stop walking.
Three steps and I'm gone. Just...

01:23:10.042 --> 01:23:11.850
Oh, God!

01:23:12.125 --> 01:23:15.984
Look, I'm just... I'm just tired

01:23:17.208 --> 01:23:21.624
of, er, of being
scared all the time

01:23:21.625 --> 01:23:24.227
and not knowing why.
I'm tired of being...

01:23:24.792 --> 01:23:29.564
Trying... Trying to
change and not knowing how.

01:23:29.917 --> 01:23:35.683
You know, leaving my latest
shit band, moving countries.

01:23:38.167 --> 01:23:42.310
Because however much I do change,

01:23:44.667 --> 01:23:46.605
I'm left with me.

01:23:52.000 --> 01:23:54.393
Sounds like you've got
it all worked out, JJ.

01:23:54.542 --> 01:23:58.732
It's logical. The reason why you wanna
die is because you don't wanna live.

01:24:00.708 --> 01:24:02.730
It's as simple as that, right?

01:24:03.083 --> 01:24:05.189
I used to think like that, too.

01:24:05.542 --> 01:24:07.149
JJ.

01:24:09.917 --> 01:24:11.749
- And then there were four.
- Don't you get it?

01:24:11.750 --> 01:24:13.874
I mean, we made it, all right?

01:24:13.875 --> 01:24:17.166
We all made it to Valentine's
Day and nothing, OK?

01:24:17.167 --> 01:24:20.066
Nothing, absolutely
nothing has changed!

01:24:21.083 --> 01:24:23.291
But everything has changed.

01:24:23.292 --> 01:24:25.360
- What?
- Everything.

01:24:26.667 --> 01:24:30.124
We are standing in entirely
different positions,

01:24:30.125 --> 01:24:32.775
for one thing.

01:24:32.958 --> 01:24:35.624
I didn't ever want to be up here again,
JJ. I'm pretty sure none of us did.

01:24:35.625 --> 01:24:40.195
He's right. You know,
it's shit up here.

01:24:40.833 --> 01:24:42.820
I... I hope...

01:24:43.875 --> 01:24:47.521
I think we still matter to you, JJ.

01:24:48.833 --> 01:24:51.898
I mean, why else would
you pick Valentine's Day?

01:24:53.250 --> 01:24:55.402
You may think you want to die,

01:24:56.583 --> 01:24:58.901
but you knew we'd look for you.

01:25:01.208 --> 01:25:03.124
We're not up here
because we wanna die.

01:25:03.125 --> 01:25:04.981
We're here for you.

01:25:05.042 --> 01:25:07.064
The Topper House Four.

01:25:07.792 --> 01:25:10.207
We belong together. We're a team.

01:25:10.208 --> 01:25:13.749
We're the worst team the world has
ever known and if I was picking,

01:25:13.750 --> 01:25:16.945
none of you would have made it
onto the subs' bench, but still,

01:25:17.000 --> 01:25:18.607
we're a team.

01:25:22.042 --> 01:25:26.102
I know, it's not much, son.

01:25:26.625 --> 01:25:33.815
But maybe we're a start.

01:25:48.250 --> 01:25:50.686
You can't even see the bottom.

01:26:14.375 --> 01:26:16.101
Hello?

01:26:17.375 --> 01:26:20.291
Hello? Can anybody hear me?

01:26:20.292 --> 01:26:22.624
We can hear you and
see you, Martin.

01:26:22.625 --> 01:26:24.791
Bonsoir, Martin.

01:26:24.792 --> 01:26:27.416
Where's the button for this?

01:26:27.417 --> 01:26:29.166
Oh, hiya.

01:26:29.167 --> 01:26:32.874
Maureen, is that
glitter on your face?

01:26:32.875 --> 01:26:35.457
No, no, no... Yes.

01:26:35.458 --> 01:26:37.374
Matty... Matty seems
to like glitter.

01:26:37.375 --> 01:26:42.082
And we're having a kind of
a... Well, New Year's Eve party.

01:26:42.083 --> 01:26:44.749
Maureen, you rager!

01:26:44.750 --> 01:26:46.582
Jess, please!

01:26:46.583 --> 01:26:49.541
I'm trying to keep the
noise down out here, OK? Shh.

01:26:49.542 --> 01:26:52.582
It was Dr Stephen's, er...
Robert's idea, actually.

01:26:52.583 --> 01:26:55.249
Yeah, he's been hugely helpful.

01:26:55.250 --> 01:26:57.124
In return for me
joining his quiz team,

01:26:57.125 --> 01:27:01.249
which has caused much controversy because
I was supposed to join another quiz team

01:27:01.250 --> 01:27:03.189
and it's kind of complicated.

01:27:03.208 --> 01:27:05.624
Sounds complicated.

01:27:05.625 --> 01:27:07.041
I saw your Dad got promoted, Jess.

01:27:07.042 --> 01:27:08.457
OK, we must have
better news than that.

01:27:08.458 --> 01:27:10.832
Come on, somebody
say something. Martin?

01:27:10.833 --> 01:27:13.541
Why don't you stoke up this party?

01:27:13.542 --> 01:27:17.567
Why don't you tell us about some of
your most recent bedtime conquests?

01:27:17.958 --> 01:27:22.315
Well, I'm often asleep by
10:00, on my own, exhausted.

01:27:22.958 --> 01:27:26.900
Are children famous for getting you
up early in the morning? I had no idea.

01:27:27.417 --> 01:27:30.707
God, when did we all turn into
Little House on the fucking Prairie?

01:27:30.708 --> 01:27:32.944
I've missed you...

01:27:33.417 --> 01:27:35.749
- All.
- You know, I, uh...

01:27:35.750 --> 01:27:39.312
I got something to
say. My therapist...

01:27:39.333 --> 01:27:40.957
Therapist? There we
go, that's some news.

01:27:40.958 --> 01:27:43.166
Did you all know JJ
is now officially mad?

01:27:43.167 --> 01:27:44.832
Er... Jess...

01:27:44.833 --> 01:27:46.582
You see a therapist, too.

01:27:46.583 --> 01:27:48.666
Yeah, of course, but all the best
people are mad, in my opinion.

01:27:48.667 --> 01:27:50.819
My therapist

01:27:51.125 --> 01:27:54.320
told me a story, a true
story about this guy

01:27:54.500 --> 01:27:56.916
who survived jumping off
the Golden Gate bridge.

01:27:56.917 --> 01:27:58.916
It's an anecdote,
it's not strictly news.

01:27:58.917 --> 01:28:04.874
The moment he jumped he realised that
the only thing in his life he couldn't fix

01:28:04.875 --> 01:28:07.276
was the thing he'd just done.

01:28:07.667 --> 01:28:11.457
I mean, can you imagine those,
those five seconds as he fell?

01:28:11.458 --> 01:28:13.666
The agony of that.

01:28:13.667 --> 01:28:15.124
Well, to me...

01:28:15.125 --> 01:28:22.397
It feels like I fell without
falling because of you guys.

01:28:23.250 --> 01:28:29.444
I had my five seconds up on
that roof and not in the air.

01:28:29.708 --> 01:28:33.401
Hmm. Five seconds.

01:28:34.583 --> 01:28:37.317
We each gave each
other five seconds.

01:28:38.250 --> 01:28:40.272
I like that, JJ.

01:28:40.542 --> 01:28:45.957
And then five seconds turned
into a year, into a life sentence.

01:28:45.958 --> 01:28:48.807
You people make me
want to kill myself.

01:28:50.417 --> 01:28:51.791
Maureen, are you coming?

01:28:51.792 --> 01:28:53.707
No, no, I'm just
talking to my friends.

01:28:53.708 --> 01:28:56.707
It's almost midnight and we're
doing the Lambada, come on.

01:28:56.708 --> 01:28:58.082
Maureen, where are you going?

01:28:58.083 --> 01:28:59.624
Maureen!

01:28:59.625 --> 01:29:00.874
Happy New Year!

01:29:00.875 --> 01:29:02.980
OK.

01:29:03.208 --> 01:29:07.457
OK, what just happened? Did Maureen just
make us look like we're the square ones?

01:29:07.458 --> 01:29:11.483
Remember, you're the one who
accused her of having too many cats.

01:29:11.542 --> 01:29:12.957
Time to sign off.

01:29:12.958 --> 01:29:14.541
Happy New Year, Jess.

01:29:14.542 --> 01:29:16.315
Happy New Year, Martin.

01:29:18.792 --> 01:29:21.442
Happy New Year, Jess.

01:29:21.917 --> 01:29:24.318
Happy New Year, John Julius.

01:29:30.708 --> 01:29:34.166
We could go to a party, you know?

01:29:34.167 --> 01:29:38.499
In case you were worried about
being upstaged by Maureen.

01:29:38.500 --> 01:29:41.249
Well, that's just the
problem, though, isn't it?

01:29:41.250 --> 01:29:43.734
I don't really want
to go to a party.

01:29:43.917 --> 01:29:45.249
Yeah.

01:29:45.250 --> 01:29:47.770
I think you've broken me.

01:29:49.583 --> 01:29:52.124
- Don't smile.
- No?

01:29:52.125 --> 01:29:53.957
- I will kill you...
- I know.

01:29:53.958 --> 01:29:56.064
If you smile.

01:30:05.167 --> 01:30:11.526
Come on. Up to bed, sleepy
head. There you go. Good girl.

01:30:14.833 --> 01:30:18.894
There you go. Oh,
yes, there you go.

01:30:19.000 --> 01:30:22.082
Is it midnight yet?

01:30:22.083 --> 01:30:25.101
Yes, it is.

01:30:25.833 --> 01:30:29.645
You made it. Another new year.

01:30:30.667 --> 01:30:32.570
Here we go.

